# So you want to travel to Sydney?

> *If you're looking to escape the cold, look no further than the land down under.*

Last year, I studied abroad at the University of Sydney and lived in the city for 5 months. Follow along to hear the best 1-week itinerary that checks all of your boxes.

## Day 1 — Check out the CBD

After checking into your hotel or Airbnb, take a walk along the water and admire the *iconic* Sydney Opera House. They have spectacular performances almost every day, and you can see what's on the schedule [here.](https://www.opera.org.au/whats-on/sydney?gad_source=1&gad_campaignid=19780411634&gbraid=0AAAAADtobcDmZtwwuUBIwiWw5X-D-ZY8T&gclid=Cj0KCQiAprLLBhCMARIsAEDhdPekKAJdfVIW4vfEcWZiGdNWk3zF1-EKjNUecdYbMfIOas8JQJzRir8aAvwYEALw_wcB)

